A: You can use String.split() method to split the string on the basis of ";" and then use String.substring() method to get the substring.
String str1 = "ashdef;I want to remove anything after the newline so my desired string would be only \"ash\".";
String[] str2 = str1.split(";");
str2 = str2[0].substring(0, str2[0].indexOf("="));


